Then we're getting into Rachel Zoe's new man Sasha Hart, a relationship coach giving me major red flags (and wait until you hear about Jennifer Aniston's boyfriend situation). Lisa Rinna just dropped a bombshell in her new book claiming Kyle and Lisa Vanderpump pushed her into the Yolanda Hadid Lyme disease storyline—and I have my own tea about Kyle trying to do something similar with me back in the day. I'm also revealing that Sophia Umansky, Nick Dubrow, and Mason Grammer are filming Next Gen LA together. In the episode recap, Kyle makes a heartbreaking confession about not feeling "seen" by Mauricio and almost filing for divorce, Dorit makes some very interesting moves to get Mo's number with visible chemistry, and we watch Kyle emotionally break down returning to her old house where the good times ended. Plus the Amanda vs. Dorit drama explodes at the birthday party when Dorit suggests Amanda used her baby loss as a manipulation tactic—and Kyle's already calling Amanda the new Crystal Minkoff. Stay until the end for my anti-inflammatory hot chocolate recipe!
